claim.claim-text:
1. A method for manufacturing a semiconductor device comprising: 
forming a first insulating film above a semiconductor substrate, said first insulating film being made of a low dielectric constant material and containing carbon; 
subjecting said first insulating film to a surface treatment to reduce the carbon concentration of a surface layer of said first insulating film, thus turning said surface layer into a low carbon concentration layer; 
forming a second insulating film on said low carbon concentration layer; 
forming a groove in said first and second insulating films for burying a metal therein; 
burying the metal in said groove formed in said first and second insulating films; and 
polishing a surface of the metal buried in said groove to form a metal wiring.

13. A semiconductor device comprising: 
a semiconductor substrate; 
an interlayer insulating film formed above said semiconductor substrate, said interlayer insulating film containing a first insulating film comprising carbon and made of a low dielectric constant material and a second insulating film formed on said first insulating film; and 
a damascene wiring structure formed in said interlayer insulating film; 
wherein said first insulating film is provided, on one surface thereof facing said second insulating film, with a low carbon concentration layer where the concentration of carbon is minimized.
